	/*
	 * nice_view_press_start.overlay
	 *
	 * Intentionally empty / no-op overlay for the nice_view_press_start shield.
	 *
	 * Background:
	 * The original overlay enabled an LS0xx SPI display node using a symbol
	 * `&nice_view_spi` and then set `zephyr,display` to point at that node.
	 * In this Corne/SSD1306 framebuffer port we do not use the LS0xx SPI
	 * display or the `&nice_view_spi` node. Leaving a reference to that
	 * undefined symbol breaks device-tree processing (gen_defines.py).
	 *
	 * Therefore this overlay is left intentionally blank so it does not inject
	 * any undefined phandles into the build. The SSD1306 framebuffer overlay
	 * used by this shield is provided in:
	 *   boards/shields/nice_view_press_start/overlay-ssd1306.dts
	 *
	 * Notes for maintainers:
	 * - If you later re-enable the original LS0xx SPI display on hardware
	 *   that actually has that controller, re-add a proper I2C/SPI controller
	 *   binding (e.g. &nice_view_spi) in the board/device overlay and then
	 *   restore the LS0xx node here.
	 *
	 * - Do NOT add a `&nice_view_spi` reference here unless the board DTS
	 *   defines that node; otherwise devicetree generation will fail.
	 */
};
